text:
1:49:38 There is no boss music, because that only plays when a monster sees you. Blind Khezu will never see you. Best chance is when another monster sees you, and Khezu is also nearby

Ive noticed that you are learning a lot of combos and moves with the weapon, you are doing great! 

I hope you are not pressured with things like a monster healing. They dont heal much, and most of the damage they take cannot be healed by eating food, only a little bit.

I think you should check out which combos flow with certain situations. Like, sometimes u walk up to a monster in axe mode, then smack it w X or A. You can use a moving strike with forward and X to reach it sooner. then combo w A A.  Sometimes you use the double charged hit w sword mode, but you can follow it up with  XA then loop back to another A or an X combo. 

Monster Hunter Rise - Charge Blade Guide (with Timestamps) << search this in youtube 

very detailed and well made guide by Rurikan. Would suggest the shield thrust stamps at 4:54 for resetting sword mode combos. dodging( side step after strike and fadeslash) at 6:28 for mobility.( these are for ruikans vid). Its a long vid, but it talks about the moves in depth and talks about practical situations for them. Just find what you need with time stamps.

You mentioned trying out other weapons later in the vid, thats also a good idea. The gaming experience changes with each weapon. Youre doing a good job learning all that charge blade stuff!

text:
DMC1 is good. Its a surprisingly complex game (tho not necessarily hard) for something that is as old as it is.

DMC3 is a classic. While 1 invented the character action genre, 3 defines it and is the standard that most games in that genre is judge on. Legit one of the most influential video game material.

DMC4 is actually also really good. The gameplay itself is an improved version of 3, which is saying a *lot*. The problem with that game, however, is that its practically only halfway finished. The game reuse of  stages and bosses is so egreggious its literally play like 6 levels and bosses, and then past halfway through the game its play that same 6 stages and bosses again but in reverse. Its a genuinely good game with an unfortunately not insignificant flaw.

DMC5 the culmination of all 5 games before it, and then adding just as much new stuffs (I didnt talk about DMC2 and the reboot DmC because that an entirely different conversation altogether). One of the best action games ever made. 

Tl,dr; 1, 3, 4, and 5 are all good. If you just want to play a DMC game, play 5. If you plan on diving into the series in its entirety, start with 1, since the games will only have more features and polish going forward, so going back from , say, DMC5 to DMC4 is gonna be pretty rough. Plus thats the best way to enjoy the story, if you care for that.
